<br>
Thank you for applying for membership in Random Acts!<br>
<br>
Have you read the call and the charter ? They're marvellous writings which will make you understand what Random Acts stands for.<br>
<br>
We want everyone to have a special friend in our guild so they don't wind up feeling lost at a later time. So we are now requiring applicants to find a sponsor from Random Acts--someone who is a regular member already. That sponsor will be responsible for you while you are a fledgling: will guide you through the fledgling period, introduce you to other members, make sure you understand our charter, and recommend you for regular membership at the end of your fledgling period. At that point the sponsor, although no longer responsible for you, has become a special friend in the guild.<br>
<br>
We have a moratorium on new members until February, so please take this time to find a sponsor and get to know some of our members.<br>
<br>
Once you have a sponsor, we need you to send (to eqrandomacts@hotmail.com) all the information about you: character name, class, race, level, your playing times, have you read the charter, and what guild task you would be interested in doing once you are a regular member. We are compiling the guild task list now, but being a sponsor is one of them.<br>
<br>
Good Journey!<br>
<br>
